The paper deals with resource allocation and scheduling for communication over fading channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of prediction models and location-based information suggests a focus on system optimization and control (cs.SY). The paper also proposes proactive policies, which may involve machine learning or optimization techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI).
